    • Constructor Detail

      • Command

        public Command(@NotNull
               @NotNull String name,
               @NotNull
               @NotNull String group,
               String description,
               IArgument... args)
        throws DuplicatedArgumentNameException
        Creates a new Command Object. Run method is required to be implemented.

        You may implement Slash to include this command as a Discord's Slash Command

        Parameters:
        name - Command name. It must be unique.
        group - Group's name. It is used by the default help command to categorize commands. It has no real effects in the engine.
        description - Command's description, It is used by the default help command to explain what the command do. It has no real effects in the engine.
        args - List of Arguments accepted by this command.
        Throws:
        DuplicatedArgumentNameException - Thrown when another Command with the same name has already been registered in the Engine

      • sendReply

        public final void sendReply(@NotNull
                            @NotNull net.dv8tion.jda.api.events.message.MessageReceivedEvent event,
                            @NotNull
                            @NotNull String reply)
        Reply to the Original Message that executed this command.

        If the command was called inside a Guild

        • If the bot has MESSAGE_HISTORY and MESSAGE_SEND permissions, it will reply referencing the original Message
        • If the bot has MESSAGE_SEND permissions, it will reply mentioning the author of the original message.
        • If the bot doesn't has any of the previous permissions, it will send a DM to the author of the original message.
        Parameters:
        event - Discord event that triggered this function call
        reply - reply message
        See Also:
        Permission, Guild
